Mansion manager David Thompson said the mansion was the ideal territory for them.
“Here in Tehriv we have a great area for bats,” he said.
We have old buildings, lots of old trees and all the right living areas.
But many things are still unknown about bats, so the work we do here and in other properties will help us understand more about what they need to thrive.”
He stressed the importance of testing the bats before carrying out maintenance work inside the properties, as the unintended destruction of a single inhabited nest could destroy up to 400 females and cubs, and could destroy an entire local population.
Bats are protected species and killing, harassing, and disturbing bats or destroying their nest areas are prohibited by law.
Elizabeth Pearl, a Scottish clerk at the Bat Conservation Foundation, encouraged the public to give a shoulder and help.
She said: "We have a lot more to learn about our bats and for many of our species we just don't know how their populations are."
